f10MonitoringMib.name: f10MonitoringMib

revisions.description: Force10 Monitoring MIB version 1.3 Added CPU Ingress Queue Unicast Statistics table.
Force10 Monitoring MIB version 1.2 Added IP and ARP statistic objects that are not available in RFC1213.

f10MonitoringMib.contactinfo: Force10 Networks, Inc 1440 McCarthy Blvd Milpitas, CA 95035 (408) 571-3500 support@force10networks.com http://www.force10networks.com
f10MonitoringMib.description: Force10 Monitoring MIB provides statistics and accounting for various Force10 products.

f10MonMibVersion.name: f10MonMibVersion
f10MonMibVersion.description: version1(1) - initial version, define QOS Queue Statistics table. version1dot1(2) - support MAC Accounting (f10MonMac). version1dot2(3) - support Interface Queue Statistics Tables (f10MonIfQueue).

f10MonMaxQueue.name: f10MonMaxQueue
f10MonMaxQueue.description: The maximum number of Force10 QOS queue supported by Force10 Interfaces.

f10InQueueStatisticsTable.name: f10InQueueStatisticsTable
f10InQueueStatisticsTable.description: The Force10 QOS Input Queue Statistics Table. This table provides Input Queue statistics for Force10 Interfaces.

f10InQueueStatisticsEntry.name: f10InQueueStatisticsEntry
f10InQueueStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the Force10 QOS Input Queue table. The Input Queue Statistics Table is indexed by the Interface and the Queue ID. The Interface index should be an valid ifIndex as defined in the RFC1213 MIB II Interface Table and the Queue ID should be a valid Force10 Queue ID.

f10InQueueId.name: f10InQueueId
f10InQueueId.description: This is the second index of this table, it must be a valid Force10 QOS Queue ID.

f10InQueueBytesCount.name: f10InQueueBytesCount
f10InQueueBytesCount.description: The cumulative number of bytes data passing through this queue. This object is available on Cyclone version 2.0 (C2T2) hardware only.

f10InQueuePktsCount.name: f10InQueuePktsCount
f10InQueuePktsCount.description: The cumulative number of packets passing through this queue. This object is available on Cyclone version 2.0 (C2T2) hardware only.

f10OutQueueStatisticsTable.name: f10OutQueueStatisticsTable
f10OutQueueStatisticsTable.description: The Force10 QOS Output Queue Statistics Table. This table provides Output Queue statistics for Force10 Interfaces.

f10OutQueueStatisticsEntry.name: f10OutQueueStatisticsEntry
f10OutQueueStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the Output Queue table. The Output Queue Statistics Table is indexed by the Interface and the Queue ID. The Interface index should be an valid ifIndex as defined in the RFC1213 MIB II Interface Table and the the Queue ID should be a valid Force10 Queue ID.

f10OutQueueId.name: f10OutQueueId
f10OutQueueId.description: This is the second index of this table, it must be a valid Force10 QOS Queue ID.

f10OutQueueBytes.name: f10OutQueueBytes
f10OutQueueBytes.description: The number of bytes in the queue. This object is available on Cyclone version 1.5 (CjTj) hardware only.

f10OutQueueBytesCount.name: f10OutQueueBytesCount
f10OutQueueBytesCount.description: The cumulative number of bytes data passing through this queue. This object is available on Cyclone version 2.0 (C2T2) hardware only.

f10WredStatisticsTable.name: f10WredStatisticsTable
f10WredStatisticsTable.description: QOS WRED Statistics Table This table provides QOS WRED statistics for the Force10 Interfaces.

f10WredStatisticsEntry.name: f10WredStatisticsEntry
f10WredStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the WRED Statistics table. The WRED Statistics Table is indexed by the Interface and the Queue ID. The Interface index should be an valid ifIndex as defined in the RFC1213 MIB II Interface Table and the Queue ID should be a valid Force10 Queue ID.

f10WredQueueId.name: f10WredQueueId
f10WredQueueId.description: This is the second index of this table, it must be a valid Force10 QOS Queue ID.

f10MacAccountingDestTable.name: f10MacAccountingDestTable
f10MacAccountingDestTable.description: The MAC Accounting Destination Table. Each entry in the table provides the MAC accounting statistics from a specific Interface, VLAN ID, and the desired destination MAC Address.

f10MacAccountingDestEntry.name: f10MacAccountingDestEntry
f10MacAccountingDestEntry.description: An entry in the MAC Accounting Destination Table. The MAC Accounting Destination table is indexed by the input Interface, VLAN ID, and the destination MAC Address.

f10MacAccInIfIndex.name: f10MacAccInIfIndex
f10MacAccInIfIndex.description: The input Interface of this entry of the table. The value should be a valid ifIndex in the MIB II Interface Table.

f10MacAccMacAddr.name: f10MacAccMacAddr
f10MacAccMacAddr.description: The MAC Address that identifies this entry of the table. This is the destination MAC Address of the packets that's going through the Interface identified by f10MacAccInIfIndex.

f10MacAccOutIfIndex.name: f10MacAccOutIfIndex
f10MacAccOutIfIndex.description: The output Interface of this entry of the table. The value should be a valid ifIndex in the MIB II Interface Table.

f10MacAccPackets.name: f10MacAccPackets
f10MacAccPackets.description: The number of packets going through this entry of the the table, identified by the Interface/MAC/VLAN.

f10MacAccBytes.name: f10MacAccBytes
f10MacAccBytes.description: The number of bytes traffic going through this entry of the table, identified by the Interface/MAC/VLAN.

f10IngQueueUnicastStatTable.name: f10IngQueueUnicastStatTable
f10IngQueueUnicastStatTable.description: The Ingress Queue Unicast Statistics Table. This table provides Queue statistics for Ingress Unicast packets between Force10 linecards.

f10IngQueueUnicastStatEntry.name: f10IngQueueUnicastStatEntry
f10IngQueueUnicastStatEntry.description: An entry in the Ingress Queue Unicast Statistics table. The Ingress Queue Unicast Statistics Table is indexed by the source and destination linecard/portpipe and Queue ID.

f10IngUnicastSrcCard.name: f10IngUnicastSrcCard
f10IngUnicastSrcCard.description: This is the source linecard number. This is the first index of this table entry.

f10IngUnicastDestCard.name: f10IngUnicastDestCard
f10IngUnicastDestCard.description: This is the destination linecard number. This is the 3rd index of this table entry.

f10IngUnicastSrcPortPipe.name: f10IngUnicastSrcPortPipe
f10IngUnicastSrcPortPipe.description: This is the Force10 Cyclone PortPipe number of the source linecard. This is the 2nd index of this table entry.

f10IngUnicastDestPortPipe.name: f10IngUnicastDestPortPipe
f10IngUnicastDestPortPipe.description: This is the Force10 Cyclone PortPipe number of the destination linecard. This is the 4th index of this table entry.

f10IngUnicastQueueId.name: f10IngUnicastQueueId
f10IngUnicastQueueId.description: This is the Queue ID of this entry. This is the 5th index of this table entry.

f10IngUnicastBytes.name: f10IngUnicastBytes
f10IngUnicastBytes.description: The number of bytes in the queue. This object is available on Cyclone version 1.5 (CjTj) hardware only.

f10IngUnicastBytesCount.name: f10IngUnicastBytesCount
f10IngUnicastBytesCount.description: The cumulative number of bytes data passing through this queue. This object is available on Cyclone version 2.0 (C2T2) and Cyclone version 3.0 (X3) hardwares only.

f10IngUnicastPacketCount.name: f10IngUnicastPacketCount
f10IngUnicastPacketCount.description: The cumulative number of packets passing through this queue. This object is available on Cyclone version 2.0 (C2T2) and Cyclone version 3.0 (X3) hardwares only.

f10IngUnicastGreenMin.name: f10IngUnicastGreenMin
f10IngUnicastGreenMin.description: The min threshold for Green packets. The min threshold identifies the queue size percentage at which the WRED dropping starts to be applied with a given configured probability.

f10IngUnicastGreenMax.name: f10IngUnicastGreenMax
f10IngUnicastGreenMax.description: The max threshold for Green packets. The max threshold identifies the queue size level at which tail drops occurs.

f10IngUnicastGreenDrop.name: f10IngUnicastGreenDrop
f10IngUnicastGreenDrop.description: The number of Green packets being dropped in this queue.

f10IngUnicastYellowMin.name: f10IngUnicastYellowMin
f10IngUnicastYellowMin.description: The min threshold for Yellow packets. The min threshold identifies the queue size percentage at which the WRED dropping starts to be applied with a given configured probability.

f10IngUnicastYellowMax.name: f10IngUnicastYellowMax

f10IngUnicastRedDrop.description: The number of Red packets being dropped in this queue.
